Join the Board of Directors
/$
$
Joining our Board of Directors offers a rewarding opportunity to make a difference while growing personally and professionally.
Expand our network by connecting with a passionate community of leaders, artists, and changemakers.
​
Make an impact while playing a meaningful role in shaping the future of an organization you care about.
​
​
Here’s what you can expect from The 5 & Dime:
Join Our Meetings: We bi-monthly to discuss plans, brainstorm ideas, and stay connected.
Be Part of Fundraising: Whether it’s helping organize an event or sharing a fundraiser with your network, your support helps keep the theatre thriving.
Committee participation: Dive into one of our working groups, like finance, marketing, or fundraising, and help us tackle exciting projects.
Spread the Word: Share your love for The 5 & Dime! Advocate for our mission and events in your circles.
Guide Our Future: Help us set goals and shape the theatre’s direction with your insights and expertise.
Make a Contribution: A yearly donation that feels meaningful to you shows your commitment to our success.
Enjoy the Shows: Join us at productions and events to support the theatre and connect with our community.
/$
$
$
$
Join a Board Committee
/$
$
As part of The 5 & Dime’s commitment to create more accessible and inclusive leadership that represents the entire Jacksonville community, we are inviting anyone who wants to become more involved to volunteer on a committee.
​
Finance & Development Committee: The work of the committee revolves around establishing specific fundraising targets, identifying funding sources, developing an action plan, tracking grants and donations, and setting ticket prices.
Governance Committee: The work of the committee revolves around board roles and responsibilities, composition, knowledge, effectiveness, and leadership.
Marketing & Outreach Committee: The work of the committee revolves around promoting the theatre, creating and maintaining partnerships, identifying special events, facilitating educational programming, and analyzing programming.
Committees meet 6 - 12 times per year, plus occasional work outside those meetings as needs arise.
The Board of Directors relies on committee work to achieve short- and long-term goals for the organization. Volunteer committee members are also prime candidates for future board positions.
Won’t you join us? If you are interested, please complete the application here by clicking the button below!

OUR STORY
/$
$
THE 5 & DIME
/$
/$
$
$
/$
$
MAKING CHANGE...
/$
$
A group of artists and friends came together with a common goal: To make a change in the Jacksonville Cultural Arts Community. From this, The 5 & Dime, A Theatre Company, was born. It started with a simple question, “Why not us?” And so we offer this: “
Why not YOU
?”
The 5 & Dime opens doors to and for all artists of all disciplines whose passion, skill, drive, and enthusiasm need a place to call home. We hope to facilitate diverse opportunities and a supportive environment to feature flourishing talent and collaboration. So, with a renewed hope in what is possible – from people just like you – we boldly set forth on this venture… come along, won’t you?
/$
/$
$
$
MISSION & VALUES
/$
/$
$
$
THE 5 & DIME TELLS STORIES THAT
ENGAGE
,
INSPIRE
,
ENTERTAIN
, AND
CHALLENGE
AUDIENCES, NURTURING A RICH ARTISTIC CULTURE IN JACKSONVILLE.
/$
$
We’re dedicated to fulfilling that mission but, as you know, we can’t do it alone. The pursuit of excellence and the ability to introduce new audiences to the power of live theatre takes the support of members from the community like you, whose very lives we seek to enrich.
/$
$
AS AN INSTITUTION, WE VALUE:
/$
$
$
PASSION
/$
$
...and we will deliver it in every story we tell.
/$
$
/$
/$
/$
$
$
CREATIVE INTEGRITY
/$
$
...and we will deliver every production at the highest levels.
/$
$
/$
$
$
COLLABORATION
/$
$
...and we will work to nurture creativity as a component of lifelong education.
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
OUR COMMUNITY
/$
$
...and we will celebrate the richness of its diversity through inclusive artistic offerings.
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
ARTISTS
/$
$
...and we will create a joyous, energetic, vibrant, and safe home for artists.
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
VOLUNTEERS, AUDIENCE,
DONORS, & STAFF
/$
$
...and recognize that they are essential partners in fulfilling our mission.
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY
/$
$
...and we recognize its importance in allowing us to create a legacy.
/$

Join us in welcoming Denise M. Reagan as the new Executive Director of The 5 & Dime
/$
$
Denise M. Reagan
has built her career as a creative and critical thinker with more than 25 years experience leading nonprofits and media companies. An award-winning writer and designer, she has been recognized for generating compelling content on multiple platforms, greatly expanding the reach of the organizations where she worked, and developing deep relationships throughout the community.
She launched her career in journalism, taking her to five different states before returning to Jacksonville to help lead one half of The Florida Times-Union newsroom. She later worked as editor of Folio Weekly, as communications director at MOCA Jacksonville, and as the first executive director of the Garden Club of Jacksonville. Denise has served on the boards of several nonprofits, including a stint as president of The 5 & Dime board in 2020-2021.
Thank you to the members of the search committee
— Bradley Akers, Krysten Bennett, Holly Gutshall, Ashli Simmons, Madelene Skinner, and Elaine Smith — who brought thoughtfulness, insight, and care to every step of the process. We appreciate you!
“
I am overjoyed to join The 5 & Dime and help the theatre take its place among the top organizations in Northeast Florida
,” Denise said. “
Stories are the juice that connects our community. Stories speak to the humanity in each of us. The 5 & Dime tells stories like no other theatre
."
We couldn’t agree more.
Here’s to bold stories, big dreams, and an exciting new chapter for The 5 & Dime
!

SUPPORT
/$
$
THE 5 & DIME
/$
/$
$
$
As a 501c3 non-profit organization, we are committed to creating theatre experiences that are accessible to all people in the community by keeping ticket prices affordable. We therefore rely on charitable contributions to help cover our essential operating costs. Without these contributions, we simply wouldn’t be here, and we wouldn’t be able to bring you the high-quality productions our community has come to enjoy.
The impact of our donors cannot be overstated. You are vitally important to us and we thank you for your generosity.

2022 SEASON
/$
$
THE 5 & DIME
/$
/$
$
$
We're pleased to welcome you to our 2022 Season! This is the first full season announcement since 2019 and our first full season since returning to our nomadic roots.
​
As theatremakers, we hold a mirror to society, showing what binds us together through our shared experiences of humanity. We had an ‘aha’ moment when we discovered the common theme between our lineup and every single person on this planet:
the power of resilience
. The characters in these plays are ordinary people experiencing extraordinary situations. They must overcome adversity and challenges, and they’ll do so through the power of resilience. Isn’t that something we’ve all experienced for the past 2 years?
​
Dates and venues will be announced soon. Until then... welcome to our 2022 Season!
